question: Ella has 7 jars of icing in her storage room. Each jar of icing can decorate 16 cupcakes. Ella wants to bake enough cupcakes to use up all of her icing. If each rack holds 14 cupcakes, how many racks worth of cupcakes should she bake?
answer:
She has enough icing for 7 * 16 = <<7*16=112>>112 cupcakes.
She needs 112 / 14 = <<112/14=8>>8 racks to bake all of the cupcakes.
#### 8
